rComments: The assignments were pretty easy but the exams can have a tricky question or two. Class can be a little boring but great at teaching. He doesn't hold office hours but does hold Q&A sessions before exams or assignment due dates. There is also no discussion board so he emails you A LOT. Overall, great prof.
Genuinely a really nice guy and one of the more useful courses I've taken.
Not gonna lie CSC336 during the first half is extremely, i mean EXTREMELY boring, huge respect for the guy for putting in the method to make it interesting.

The assignments this year were a joke, he more or less gave us the answers via email if you waited long enough. It was hard to study for the tests because we didn't have any practice problems throughout the course. The lectures weren't very organized and overall the pace was slow. Easy course but not very fun.

Good prof, very easy going. He goes through the materials at a very well-paced and constant speed, very easy to follow and understand. General style isn't all that exciting, but definitely teaches the materials well.

Excellent instructor. Very lucid and engaging when presenting material. Minimal use of textbook because notes are very thorough. The level of assignments is slightly more difficult but fairly reflects the material. Good course!

Easy going and nice prof. Don't focus too much the past test and final chances are u'll be facing a similar but different style of questions. Learn the essential from them but not hard-study to them. Mindful about the details of he emphasis on they could be a strong hints. He'll also guide u through in emails and extra Q&A sessions for your HW.
